sentences: Patrick Donohue (born April 28, 1953) is an American fingerstyle guitarist born in St. Paul, Minnesota.
Donohue grew up in St. Paul but moved to Denver, Colorado in 1971 to study at Regis College (now Regis University).
After his graduation in 1975, he returned to Denver.
In 1985 Donohue's first album, Manhattan to Memphis, was released by Red House.
In 1982 he was runner-up in the National Fingerpicking Championship at the Walnut Valley Festival in Winfield, Kansas.
In 2008 the Martin Guitar Company released a signature model, the OM-30DB Pat Donohue Custom Edition.
